{
  "doc_id": "15223",
  "text": "Note that for k ∈ 1/2 + Z the space M k,ρ of holomorphic modular forms of weight k for ρ is isomorphic to the space J * k+1/2,N of skew-holomorphic Jacobi forms of weight k + 1/2 and index N , and M k,ρ is isomorphic to the space J k+1/2,N of holomorphic Jacobi forms of weight k + 1/2 and index N (see [CITATION_1] , Section 5). In particular, one can view θ 1/2 and θ 3/2 as skew-holomorphic Jacobi forms of weight 1 and 2. Further, we will make frequent use of a result by Skoruppa which asserts that M 1/2,ρ ∼ = J 1,N = {0} for all N (see [CITATION_2] , Theorem 5.7).",
